'''Birra Menabrea''' is an Italian [[Brewery|brewing company]] located in [[Biella]], [[Piedmont]]. Under this label - distributed since the early nineties by the [[Forst (brewery)|Birra Forst]], but owned by the Thedy family (heir of the founders of the company) - around 100 thousand hectolitres of beer are produced annually, part of which for export in twenty countries.
