{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Gewinn | image_file = Gewinn-Magazin-Logo.svg | image_size = | image_caption = Logo of ''Gewinn'' | editor = | editor_title = | frequency = Monthly (11 times a year) | circulation = 80,254 (2010-2011) | category = [[Business journalism|Business magazine]] | company =Wailand & Waldstein GmbH | publisher = Wailand & Waldstein GmbH | founded = {{start date and age|1982}} | firstdate = | country =Austria | based =[[Vienna]] | language = [[German language|German]] | website = {{url|https://www.gewinn.com/}} | issn = | oclc = }}
'''''Gewinn''''' is a [[German language]] business [[magazine]] published in [[Austria]] and based in [[Vienna]].
==History and profile== ''Gewinn'' was launched in 1982 by Wailand & Waldstein GmbH.<ref name=gwinn>{{cite web|title=What is Gewinn?|url=http://www.schoolgames.de/download/at/Partner_Profil_Gewinn_EN.pdf|work=Gewinn|accessdate=8 October 2013}}</ref><ref name=char/> Georg Waldstein and Georg Wailand are the owners of the magazine<ref name=char/> which is published by Wailand & Waldstein company.<ref name=rustel/><ref name=fip/> The magazine has its headquarters in Vienna.<ref name=gwinn/>
''Gewinn'', published 11 times per year, has the following main sections: Money and stock market, management and careers, [[Information technology|IT]] and innovations, real estate, law and taxes and leisure and lifestyle.<ref name=gwinn/> Since 1985 it provides its [[subscribers]] with a [[Supplement (publishing)|supplement]], ''Gewinn extra''.<ref name=char>{{cite web|author=Charlotte Natmeßnig|title=Business Press in Austria|url=http://www.helsinki.fi/iehc2006/papers2/Natmessn.pdf|work=Helsinki.fi|format=Conference Paper|date=2006|accessdate=12 December 2014|}}</ref> The magazine develops several rankings in regard to Austrian business institutes and figures.<ref>{{cite web|title=QuantaRed News|url=http://www.quantared.com/news/46-quantared-has-climbed-into-the-top-10-start-up-companys|work=QuantaRed|accessdate=8 October 2013}}</ref>
Michael Fembek served as the [[editor-in-chief]] of the magazine from 2000 to 2007.<ref>{{cite web|title=Speakers’ bios|url=http://www.snf.org/texts/uploads/files/Speakers%20Bios.pdf|work=Stavros Niarchos Foundation|accessdate=8 October 2013}}</ref>
==Circulation== In the late 1980s ''Gewinn'' became a serious competitor to another Austrian business magazine, ''[[Trend (magazine)|Trend]]''.<ref name=char/> ''Gewinn'' had a circulation of 65,000 copies in 2003 and 62,000 copies in the first quarter of 2004.<ref name=rustel>{{cite web|title=Media Markets: Austria Country Overview|url=http://oldtelecoms.kondrashov.ru/world/austria.html|work=Russian Telecom|accessdate=1 January 2015|date=August 2004}}</ref> Its 2005 circulation was 60,462 copies.<ref name=char/> In 2006 the magazine had a circulation of 95,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Austria. Gewinn |url=http://www.igpmedia.com/countrydetail.asp?place=Austria&mediaid=Gew1 |work=İGP Media |accessdate=1 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402095231/http://www.igpmedia.com/countrydetail.asp?place=Austria&mediaid=Gew1 |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> For the first half of 2007 the magazine's circulation was 53,777 copies, whereas it was 55,453 copies for the same period in 2008.<ref>{{cite web|title=Austria: New circulation figures for the 1st half 2008|url=http://www.publicitas.com/en/home/media-news-events/news-detail/?newsid=24173&title=austria-new-circulation-figures-for-the-1st-half-2008#.UlQTYmRJVgs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131014172112/http://www.publicitas.com/en/home/media-news-events/news-detail/?newsid=24173&title=austria-new-circulation-figures-for-the-1st-half-2008#.UlQTYmRJVgs|dead-url=yes|archive-date=14 October 2013|work=Publicitas|accessdate=8 October 2013|date=20 August 2008}}</ref> The 2010 circulation of the magazine was 76,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|title=Western Europe Media Facts. 2011 Edition|url=http://conan.lib.muohio.edu/ebooks/Western_Europe_Market_MediaFact/2011/Western%20Europe%20Market%20&%20MediaFact%202011.pdf|work=ZenithOptimedia|accessdate=6 March 2016}}</ref> The magazine was read by 275,000 people in the period of 2010-2011.<ref name=gwinn/> During the same period the magazine had a circulation of 80,254 copies.<ref name=fip>{{cite web|title=World Magazine Trends 2010/2011 |url=http://www.revistas-ari.com/attachments/209_WMT_2010_2011_Europe.pdf |work=FIPP |accessdate=31 March 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402165145/http://www.revistas-ari.com/attachments/209_WMT_2010_2011_Europe.pdf |archivedate=2 April 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref>
