{{Infobox person |name = Robby Enthoven |image = |image_size = |caption = |birth_name = Robert Adrian Graham Enthoven |birth_date = May 1968 |birth_place = South Africa |death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> |death_place = |residence = |nationality = South African |ethnicity = |citizenship = |other_names = |known_for = CEO of [[Nando's]] |education = |alma_mater = |occupation = |years_active = |home_town = |salary = |networth = |title = |term = |predecessor = |successor = |boards = |religion = |spouse = |partner = |children = |parents = [[Dick Enthoven]] |relations = [[Patrick Enthoven]] (grandfather) |website = }}
'''Robert Adrian Graham Enthoven''' (born May 1968) is a South African/Dutch businessman, managing director of the casual dining chicken chain, [[Nando's]].
Robert Adrian Graham Enthoven was born in May 1968, and has South African/Dutch nationality.<ref name=CompaniesHouse>{{cite web|title=Nando's Chicken Limited|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/company/00166821/officers|website=Companies House|accessdate=29 October 2015}}</ref> He is the son of the billionaire owner of Nando's, [[Dick Enthoven]], and also goes by the name of Robert T'hooft, T'hooft being his mother's maiden name.<ref name=Telegraph>{{cite news|last1=Goodley|first1=Simon|title=City Diary|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/comment/citydiary/2851810/City-Diary.html|accessdate=29 October 2015|work=Daily Telegraph|date=14 May 2003}}</ref>
Robby Enthoven has been managing director of Nando's since 1993, when there were just two branches. As of 2018, there are over 400 restaurants in the UK.<ref name=Caterer>{{cite news|title=Caterer and Hotelkeeper 100: Robby Enthoven, Nando's|url=https://www.thecaterer.com/articles/346578/caterer-and-hotelkeeper-100-robby-enthoven-nandos|accessdate=29 October 2015|work=The Caterer|date=6 December 2012}}</ref>
