'''Vladimir Filat''' (born 6 May 1969), commonly referred to as '''Vlad Filat''' ({{IPA-ro|vlad fiˈlat|pron}}), is a [[Moldova]]n businessman and politician, founder of [[Liberal Democratic Party of Moldova]]. He was the [[Prime Minister of Moldova]] from 25 September 2009 to 25 April 2013. He also was appointed as the [[Presidents of Moldova|Interim President]] of Moldova for a brief period of time in 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://unimedia.info/stiri/-13413.html | title=Guvernul Filat a fost investit cu votul a 53 de deputaţi AIE. Şeful SIS a fos demis de către Parlament. Noul director este Mihai Gheorghe | date=2009-09-25 | accessdate=2013-05-10}}</ref>

==Education and early career==
Vlad is the second child of Maria and Vasile Filat and was born on May 6, 1969, in [[Lăpușna, Hîncești|Lăpușna]], a commune in the [[Moldavian Soviet Socialist Republic|Moldavian SSR]]. Alongside his two sisters (Ala and Valentina) and brother Ion, Vlad grew up in a part of Lăpușna called "Talcioc". In 1986, he graduated from high school in his hometown. Between 1986 and 1987, he worked at the school radio station until he was called up for military service. He carried out his [[compulsory military service]] in the [[Soviet Army]] (May 8, 1987 — August 15, 1989), in [[Simferopol]] and [[Sevastopol]]. He activated in [[KGB]] [[Soviet Border Troops]], having the rank of [[private first class]] and being decorated by his KGB superiors.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ziaristionline.ro/2011/01/28/vladimir-vlad-filat-premierul-moldovei-recrut-fruntas-in-trupele-kgb-foto/|title=Vladimir (Vlad) Filat, premierul Moldovei, recrut fruntas in trupele KGB.|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>

From 1989 to 1990, he studied at the Cooperation College (''Kooperativny [[Technikum (Polish education)|technikum]]'') of [[Chișinău]], going on to study law at the [[University of Iași]] (1990–1994). As a student, he was the leader of the "League of students from Bessarabia in Romania", an organization formed by Moldovan students in [[Romania]]. In [[Iași]], among his classmates was [[Alexandru Tănase]]. While he was a student in Iași, he met his wife Sanda in the autumn of 1991; they dated for only three months before they married.

Between 1994–1998, Vlad Filat initiated and conducted more business in Romania. He was general director of "RoMold Trading SRL" in Iași (1994–1997) and the president of the Administrative Council of "Dosoftei" company in Iași (1997–1998).

==Early political activity==
Filat was a member of the [[Democratic Party of Moldova]] from 1997, when the party was founded, until 2007.

Having returned to [[Moldova]] for good in 1998, he was appointed general director of the Department of Privatization and State Property Administration from the Ministry of Economy and Reform of the [[Government of the Republic of Moldova]] (1998-1999).

He was a State minister in the [[Ion Sturza]] [[Cabinet of Moldova|cabinet]] of [[Alliance for Democracy and Reforms]] from 12 March 1999 to 12 November 1999.

In 2000, Filat was elected Vice-President of the Democratic Party. In the [[Moldovan parliamentary election, 2005|2005 parliamentary election]], he became a member of the [[Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|Moldovan Parliament]]. Until March 2009, he was Vice-President of the Parliamentary Commission for Security, Public Order, and Defense. He was also a member of the [[European Union|EU]]-Moldova Parliamentary Cooperation Committee.

He ran for [[Mayor of Chișinău]] in the [[Moldovan local election, 2007|2007 local election]] and won 8.32% of the vote, in fourth place. Soon after the local election, in September 2007, he left the Democratic Party after ten years of political activity inside the party.

Filat has been the President of the [[Liberal Democratic Party of Moldova]] since December 2007.

== Moldovan parliamentary election, 2009 ==
{{main|Moldovan parliamentary election, April 2009|Moldovan parliamentary election, July 2009}}
In the [[Moldovan parliamentary election, April 2009|April 2009 parliamentary election]], his party won 15 seats and in the [[Moldovan parliamentary election, July 2009|July 2009 parliamentary election]] [[Liberal Democratic Party of Moldova|PLDM]] became the second party in the country with 18 seats and the first party within the [[Alliance For European Integration]].

== Alliance for European Integration ==
{{main|Alliance for European Integration}}

After the July 2009 parliamentary election, alongside [[Mihai Ghimpu]], [[Marian Lupu]], and [[Serafim Urechean]], Vlad Filat signed the [[Alliance For European Integration]] in a press-conference on August 8, 2009. Towards the end of August 2009, he became the candidate of the Alliance For European Integration for the post of [[Prime Minister of Moldova]].

== Prime Minister ==
{{main|Prime Minister of Moldova|Cabinet of Moldova|Vlad Filat Cabinet (disambiguation){{!}}Vlad Filat Cabinet}}

The [[Constitutional Court of Moldova]] confirmed earlier on September 17, 2009 the legitimacy of [[Mihai Ghimpu]]'s position as [[Acting President of Moldova]], which gave him the right to nominate a prime minister. On the same day, Ghimpu signed a decree nominating Filat for the office of prime minister. Earlier on September 17, the [[Moldovan Parliament|parliament]] approved a new government structure; according to the draft structure, the number of ministries remains unchanged at 16 but their names and responsibilities have been changed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.antena3.ro/stiri/moldova/parlamentul-republicii-moldova-a-aprobat-structura-noului-guvern-vlad-filat-noul-premier_80430.html|title=Parlamentul Republicii Moldova a aprobat structura noului Guvern: Vlad Filat, noul premier|publisher=}}</ref>

The Alliance for European Integration gave a vote of confidence to the [[First Filat Cabinet|new government]] headed by PM Vladimir Filat at a plenary meeting on September 25, 2009.

On March 8, 2013 Filat was [[2013 Moldovan government crisis|dismissed]] by motion of censure following charges of corruption, abuse of power and influence peddling.<ref>[http://www.parlament.md/LegislationDocument.aspx?Id=928a2109-946a-4dfa-8caf-797bb43620c3 Moțiune de cenzură asupra activității Guvernului]</ref> In spite of this, President [[Nicolae Timofti]] decreed that members of the government should continue to exert their public duties until a new government were to be formed.<ref>[http://lex.justice.md/index.php?action=view&view=doc&lang=1&id=347106 Decretul nr. 534-VII, privind demisia Guvernului]</ref>

Subsequently, on April 10, 2013 the President nominated Vlad Filat as a candidate for Prime Minister, authorizing him with the mission of forming a new government.
However, on April 22, 2013, the Constitutional Court ruled that this decree is unconstitutional, stating that a Prime Minister ousted by vote of no confidence following suspicions of corruption cannot further perform this duty and that the President has the constitutional obligation to appoint in the interim capacity a member of the government whose integrity was not affected.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.constcourt.md/libview.php?l=ro&idc=7&id=428&t=/Prezentare-generala/Serviciul-de-presa/Noutati/Mentinerea-in-functie-a-Prim-ministrului-unui-Guvern-demis-pentru-motive-de-coruptie-este-neconstitutionala|title=Menţinerea în funcţie a Prim-ministrului unui Guvern demis pentru motive de corupţie este neconstituţională|publisher=}}</ref>

The President appointed [[Iurie Leancă]] as Acting Prime Minister on April 25, 2013.

== Arrest and accusations of corruption ==
Filat was stripped of his immunity and handcuffed in parliament on October 15, 2015.<ref name="Reuters">{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-moldova-protests-filat-idUSKCN0S91BY20151015|title=Moldova detains former PM in parliament over $1 billion fraud|author=Alexander Tanas|date=15 October 2015|work=Reuters}}</ref> He was investigated for the [[$1 billion bank fraud]] and accused of having taken bribes of about $250 million from [[Ilan Shor]], who was chairman of the board at Savings Bank from April to November 28, 2014.

Filat has denied wrongdoing and said the allegations against him are politically motivated.<ref name="Radio Free Europe Radio Liberty">{{cite web|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/moldova-ex-pm-immunity-lifted-fraud-probe/27308192.html|title=Moldova's Ex-PM Detained After Parliament Lifts His Immunity|work=RadioFreeEurope/RadioLiberty}}</ref>

On June 27, 2016, Vlad Filat was sentenced to 9 years in prison.

==Honours==

In December 2013 Filat was awarded by the [[President of Moldova]] [[Nicolae Timofti]] with the highest distinction in Moldova, "[[Order of the Republic (Moldova)|Order of the Republic]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.publika.md/vlad-filat-a-fost-decorat-cu-ordinul-republicii--uite-pentru-ce-merite_1741431.html|title=Vlad Filat a fost decorat cu "Ordinul Republicii". |date=17 June 2015|work=PUBLIKA.MD|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>

On 25 November 2014 Filat was awarded by the [[President of Romania]] [[Traian Băsescu]] with [[Order of Faithful Service|National Order of Faithful Service]] of level Grand Cross.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ziarulnational.md/presedintele-basescu-i-a-acordat-o-distinctie-lui-vlad-filat/|title=Președintele Băsescu le-a acordat DISTINCȚII lui Vlad Filat, deputatei Maria Ciobanu și scriitorului Iulian Filip|work=ziarulnational.md|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>

In November 2013 Filat was awarded by the then-[[President of Georgia]] [[Mikheil Saakashvili]], with one of the highest distinctions in the country – the Order of Excellence.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.timpul.md/articol/vlad-filat-a-fost-decorat-de-saakasvili-51812.html|title=Vlad Filat a fost decorat de Saakașvili|work=Timpul - Știri din Moldova|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Filat has divorced Sanda Filat in August 2012, a [[psychologist]]. They have two children: Luca (b. 1995) and Iustina (b. 1998).<ref name="copii">{{cite web|url=http://protv.md/stiri/entertainment/la-brat-cu-cei-doi-copii-ai-sai-cum-a-aparut-sanda-filat-la-ceremonia---477131.html |title=La brat cu cei doi copii ai sai. Cum a aparut Sanda Filat la ceremonia de lansare a fundatie Bach |publisher=ProTV.md |date=2014-03-21 |accessdate=2014-03-28}}</ref>
In January 2014, Vlad Filat married former [[Pro TV Chișinău]] presenter<ref>[http://protv.md/stiri/entertainment/angela-gonta-se-retrage-de-la-pupitrul-stirilor-vedeta-pro-tv---246291.html Angela Gonta se retrage de la pupitrul stirilor. Vedeta PRO TV se marita cu Vlad Filat], [[Pro TV Chișinău]], 15.12.2013 19:51</ref> [[Angela Gonța]].<ref name="CunAdevărul">{{cite web|url=http://adevarul.ro/moldova/actualitate/vlad-filat-angela-gonta-fost-cununati-manastirea-curchi-mitropolitul-vladimir-1_52f259ecc7b855ff5618f24a/index.html|title=Vlad Filat și Angela Gonța au fost cununați la Mănăstirea Curchi de Mitropolitul Vladimir|work=adevarul.ro|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref><ref name="CunJurnal">[http://jurnal.md/ro/news/vlad-filat-i-angela-gon-a-s-au-cununat-1163290/ Vlad Filat și Angela Gonța s-au cununat]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://inprofunzime.md/stiri/politic/vlad-filat-si-angela-gonta-s-au-casatorit-cine-le-au-fost-nasii.html |title=Vlad Filat si Angela Gonta s-au casatorit! Anuntul facut de politician: Cine le-au fost nasi |publisher=Inprofunzime.md |date=2013-12-27 |accessdate=2014-02-06}}</ref> In June 2014<ref>[http://ziarulnational.md/angela-gonta-a-nascut/ Angela Gonța a NĂSCUT], ziarulnational.md</ref> Vlad Filat and Angela Gonța became parents, with birth of their girl Ekaterina.<ref name=copilFB>{{cite web|url=http://www.facebook.com/angela.gonta/posts/802127959811074|title=Facebook|work=facebook.com|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=copilperfecte>{{cite web|url=http://perfecte.md/article/family/poarta-numele-unei-sfinte-iata-cum-o-cheama-pe-fetita-angelei---588381.html|title=Poarta numele unei sfinte! Iata cum o cheama pe fiica Angelei Gonta si a lui Vlad Filat|work=perfecte.md|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=copilpentruea>{{cite web|url=http://pentruea.md/article/angela-gonta-si-vlad-filat-au-dezvaluit-prenumele-copilului-iata-cum-se-numeste-fetita--6386.html|title=Angela Gonța și Vlad Filat au dezvăluit prenumele copilului! Iată cum se numește fetița!|work=ea.md|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=copilkankan>{{cite web|url=http://www.kankan.md/cum-si-a-numit-angela-gonta-fetita-jurnalista-a-scris-un-mesaj-emotionant-pe-facebook/|title=Cum și-a numit Angela Gonța fetița! Jurnalista a scris un mesaj emoționant pe Facebook|work=kankan|accessdate=17 June 2015}}</ref>

